    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Nahua ritual calendar. Literally "count of days." It was made up of twenty periods of thirteen days ("trecenas") which together made up a cycle of two hundred and sixty days. Each day had its own denomination, formed by the combination of a number (from one to thirteen) and twenty different signs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Calendario ritual nahua. Literalmente "cuenta de los días". Se componía de veinte períodos de trece días (trecenas) que juntos, formaban un ciclo de doscientos sesenta días. Cada día tenía su propia denominación, formada por la combinación de un número (del uno al trece) y veinte signos diferentes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tonalpohualli campeca nahuatl. Quence "tlapohualiztli tlen tonatiuh". Eliyaya cempohualli periodos tlen mahtlactli huan eyi tonatiuh (trecenas) quitl zancehco eliyaya ce ciclo tlen ome ciento huan epohualli tonatiuh. Cehce tonatiuh quipiyaya itlamanextil, mochihchihuayaya quemman momaneloyaya ce tlapohualiztli (tlen ce azta mahtlactli huan eyo) huan cempohualli tlaixnextilli tlen axcehca.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
